init_text: When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It's your life, and you are watching it from beginning to end.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You were the worst, you realise now.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Is this just some cruel joke?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Or is this the way you are supposed to learn from your mistakes.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are going to make sure that this next life is the best possible.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You watch for hours, maybe days, or years.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look at your former selves, most of them are nodding their heads and saying, yes.
